Had a great time at London Eye and the River Cruise. Friendly staff and well organised process. There was a bit of queue, but it went through relatively quickly (circa 20 minutes).

Our tour guide on the River Cruise (Liam) was amazing. Made the 45 mins ride on the boat worthwhile. Stayed in the top compartment and was blessed to see so much history the city has to offer. Will definitely recommend a visit when in the area.

One tip for London Eye which was fairly obvious - if a group photo is desirable, everyone should face the same camera during the photo session towards the end of your journey. There are two cameras in the cabin, we didn't all look in the same direction and ended paying for an extra photo!

I'm giving this 4* because of the ridiculous way crowds are managed during a pandemic. The experience itself was nice, bird's eye view of the city and beyond, if a tad expensive (but this is London, so...) We used 2-4-1 offers so not too bad.
